    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Lisa, so glad they worked for you.  And with raspberries, chocolate chips, and some cocoa &#8211; genius!</></>And shelly, I&#8217;m very sorry to hear of your trouble.  I know well what you mean &#8211; with frozen fruit, this dough can be VERY, very sticky.  I had to add a bit of extra flour on the board when I kneaded them, but still, they were sticky.  Mine didn&#8217;t fall flat, though, upon baking, so I&#8217;m really not sure what to tell you there.  My apologies.</></>All told, this recipe is easiest and most predictable when you use a non-wet add-in, such as currants, nuts, or other dried fruits.  I did like it quite a bit with frozen strawberries, but it was messy, and these days, I tend to stick with dried fruits instead.</p>
