    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>After finding this recipe in your book (which I am devouring &#8211; kudos!) I made a batch of lemon-ginger-dried cranberry ones this afternoon. Loved them! I used cake flour (adding 1 Tbsp per cup of all-purpose) because that&#39;s all I had in my pantry (just HAD to bake a batch today!!), and they came out fluffy but almost spongy. But the flavor was fresh and terrific; I&#39;ll leave out the cranberries &#8211; they were superfluous, really &#8211; next time and use all-purpose flour. Great alternative to my usual buttermilk scones!</p>
